
[1]nakedness

   NAKEDNESS, n.

   1. Want of covering or clothing; nudity; bareness.

   2. Want of means of defense.

   Ye are spies; to see the nakedness of the land are ye come. Gen 42.

   3. Plainness; openness to view.

   To uncover nakedness, in Scripture, is to have incestuous or unlawful
   commerce with a female.
